    <item>
      <title>Digital Rights Charter - Windows Free Religion - Do you even #Web3, bruh?</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/posts/digital-rights-charter/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 17 Mar 2024 10:45:16 -0400</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/posts/digital-rights-charter/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;castgarden-video&#34;&gt;CastGarden Video&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;iframe title=&#34;Digital Rights Charter - Windows Free Religon - Do you even #Web3, bruh?  - UB Live 32623&#34; width=&#34;100%&#34; height=&#34;450&#34; src=&#34;https://cast.garden/videos/embed/172c0567-c03d-4c4d-9cea-44fdacefb379&#34; frameborder=&#34;0&#34; allowfullscreen=&#34;&#34; sandbox=&#34;allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-popups&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://castgardn7yj746n7nyt3udot5orhpqfs36sl7rq2y3yd4su6ruuddyd.onion/w/3RXE2TsJnmQadkb4nqoyoM&#34;&gt;Click here to watch this video on Tor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Originally published December 2023&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&#xA;UPDATE in March of 2024:&#xA;I discussed a lot of different things in this episode. A lot of which did not pan out regarding a decentralized radio station. I am still considering them. If you know of some real decentralized solution to a internet radio stream please let me know. Especially if it does not involve crypto currency as a solution. Crypto currency is awesome but you cant just slap it onto a centralized service and call it decentralized or Web3. Lipstick on a pig is still a fucking pig.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
